WEBVTT

00:05.873 --> 00:07.341
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:07.374 --> 00:10.978
YOU COME ANYWHERE NEAR MY
CHILDREN, I'LL KILL YOU MYSELF.

00:11.011 --> 00:14.147
OR PERHAPS ‐‐
[ GASPS ]

00:14.181 --> 00:16.183
I COULDN'T FIND
A GOLF CLUB.

00:18.051 --> 00:20.988
WE NEED TO BE OUT OF HERE
IN FIVE.

00:21.021 --> 00:22.689
YOU KILLED SOMEONE?
YEAH.

00:22.723 --> 00:23.690
HOLY SHIT, SHANE.

00:28.295 --> 00:29.062
I LOVE YOU.

00:29.096 --> 00:30.364
Gayle:
I LOVE YOU MORE.

00:30.397 --> 00:32.833
ANDY: I love her.
But I ran.

00:32.866 --> 00:35.035
Did you happen to abandon her
with your keys in your pocket?

00:35.068 --> 00:36.637
No.
She loves driving the van.

00:36.670 --> 00:39.673
MY CHILD MURDERED SOMEONE.
I HAVE TO LEAVE TOWN NOW.

00:39.706 --> 00:42.976
ALL HE WANTS TO DO IS
FOLLOW YOU DOWN YOUR NEXT
CROOKED ROAD. IT'S OVER.

00:43.010 --> 00:45.512
YOU CAN COME IF YOU WANT.
I'D LIKE YOU TO COME.

00:45.546 --> 00:47.681
YOU HAVE TO GET BUBBIE'S RING
BACK FROM AUDRA.

00:47.714 --> 00:48.982
NO RING.
JUST DRIVE.

00:49.016 --> 00:50.484
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

01:09.970 --> 01:12.840
SO, WHAT'S THE DESTINATION,
BOSS?

01:12.873 --> 01:14.441
THAT'S THE THIRD TIME
YOU'VE ASKED THAT.

01:14.474 --> 01:15.776
THIRD TIME'S THE CHARM.

01:15.809 --> 01:17.211
NORTH.

01:17.244 --> 01:18.345
NANCE.

01:18.378 --> 01:22.082
RIGHT NOW, IT'S DESTINATION
"AWAY FROM WHERE WE WERE."

01:23.617 --> 01:26.854
DID SHE SCREAM?

01:26.887 --> 01:28.722
WAS THERE LOTS OF BLOOD?

01:28.755 --> 01:30.891
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

01:30.924 --> 01:32.960
ARE YOU TOTALLY FREAKED

01:32.993 --> 01:35.229
THAT THE FRUIT OF YOUR LOINS
IS A KILLER FRUIT?

01:37.664 --> 01:40.801
THE BLOW TO THE HEAD WASN'T
NECESSARILY THE CAUSE OF DEATH.

01:40.834 --> 01:43.604
OH, YEAH, MIGHT'VE BEEN
THAT HARD FALL INTO THE POOL.

01:45.873 --> 01:48.008
MM. MAYBE.

01:48.041 --> 01:49.743
I DON'T KNOW.

01:49.776 --> 01:50.944
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

01:50.978 --> 01:54.681
OKAY. I SEE. YEAH.
MORE TIME. MORE DISTANCE.

01:54.715 --> 01:56.416
I CAN WAIT.

01:56.450 --> 01:59.953
CHANGE OF TOPIC.
UM, AUDRA ‐‐ LOVE OF MY LIFE?

01:59.987 --> 02:01.054
[ SCOFFS ]

02:01.088 --> 02:03.023
[ IMITATES SCOFF ]
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

02:03.056 --> 02:05.259
[ IMITATES SCOFF ]

02:08.962 --> 02:11.164
[ IMITATES SCOFF ]

02:11.198 --> 02:13.901
WHAT EXACTLY
ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

02:13.934 --> 02:16.170
"MEDIA MOGUL,
UNFORTUNATE ACCIDENT."

02:16.203 --> 02:17.771
"MUERTE, PILAR ZUAZO."

02:17.804 --> 02:19.706
THERE'S NOTHING HERE.

02:19.740 --> 02:22.209
PROBABLY TOMORROW.

02:29.683 --> 02:30.517
I'M HUNGRY.

02:30.551 --> 02:32.853
YOU SWUNG A MALLET
AT A WOMAN'S HEAD.

02:32.886 --> 02:35.155
YEAH.

02:35.189 --> 02:36.857
AND YOU'RE OKAY
WITH THAT?

02:36.890 --> 02:38.458
MM‐HMM.

02:41.662 --> 02:44.831
MAYBE SHE'S NOT DEAD.
MAYBE SHE'S JUST INJURED.

02:44.865 --> 02:47.000
SHE MIGHT'VE BEEN
JUST INJURED

02:47.034 --> 02:50.237
BEFORE MOM SENT THE AUTOMATIC
POOL COVER OVER HER.

02:52.506 --> 02:55.275
Andy: IT'S TIME FOR ME TO SAY,
"WHAT IS IT THAT I REALLY WANT?"

02:55.309 --> 02:57.311
CHANGE THE BABY.
YOU GOT IT.

02:57.344 --> 02:59.379
TWO SECONDS.
I'M SO FAST.

02:59.413 --> 03:01.615
[ DIALS ]

03:01.648 --> 03:02.916
FEMALE VOICE:
Message one.

03:02.950 --> 03:04.251
ESTEBAN:
I want to know where you are

03:04.284 --> 03:06.820
<i>and when you'll be back.</i>

03:06.854 --> 03:08.188
I want to know where my boy is.

03:08.222 --> 03:09.690
Call m‐‐
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

03:17.030 --> 03:18.332
LISTEN.

03:18.365 --> 03:21.969
LOGIC SAYS, IF HE'S MADE
SEASONAL LOGGING HIS LIFE ‐‐

03:22.002 --> 03:23.670
LET'S GO!

03:23.704 --> 03:24.938
YES. ONE SECOND.

03:24.972 --> 03:26.907
IF HE'S OFF FELLING AND SWAMPING
SIX MONTHS A YEAR,

03:26.940 --> 03:28.041
THAT'S A MESSAGE.

03:28.075 --> 03:29.776
HE'S NOT READY.
I SAID LET'S FUCKING GO.

03:29.810 --> 03:33.013
SO, YOU GOT TO SAY, "HEY,
WHAT DOES DEB WANT FOR DEB?"

03:33.046 --> 03:35.115
[ HORN HONKS ]
DO YOU HAVE E‐MAIL, DEB?
'CAUSE WE CAN TYPE IT OUT.

03:35.148 --> 03:37.584
I GOTTA GO.
YOU DESERVE EVERYTHING GOOD!

03:37.618 --> 03:41.121
KEEP STRONG, SISTER!

03:44.758 --> 03:46.760
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

03:46.793 --> 03:49.463
YOU PAID FOR THAT
WITH CASH, RIGHT?

03:49.496 --> 03:50.597
CARD.

03:50.631 --> 03:53.200
OH, GREAT.
PERFECT.

03:53.233 --> 03:56.570
CHARGES WILL BE ONLINE IN,
WHAT, AN HOUR?

03:56.603 --> 03:58.071
HE'S GONNA SEE.
[ SIGHS ]

03:58.105 --> 04:00.741
THERE, THERE, THERE.
SUPERSTORES. LET'S STOCK UP.

04:00.774 --> 04:02.142
PULL OFF.
WHAT?

04:02.176 --> 04:03.277
IT'S NOW OR NEVER.

04:03.310 --> 04:05.045
MAX OUT THE CARDS,
SNAP 'EM,

04:05.078 --> 04:06.880
AND DRIVE LIKE FUCK SO WE'RE
NOWHERE NEAR THIS PLACE.

04:06.914 --> 04:08.615
OKAY, THAT'S SMART.

04:08.649 --> 04:11.852
I MISSED THE EXIT. SHIT.
I'LL ‐‐ I'LL DOUBLE BACK.

04:11.885 --> 04:14.588
SHIT. SH‐‐ SHIT.

04:14.621 --> 04:17.491
SHIT!

04:17.524 --> 04:19.726
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
THEY OPEN THE POOL COVER?

04:23.864 --> 04:25.666
THEY FOUND HER
AND SHE'S DEAD, RIGHT?

04:28.869 --> 04:31.205
[ SIGHS ]
WE NEED TO GO BACK.

04:31.238 --> 04:33.774
WE CAN'T GO BACK.
YES, WE CAN.

04:33.807 --> 04:36.109
WE CAN EXPLAIN IT.
HE'S A JUVENILE.

04:36.143 --> 04:38.445
WE DON'T HAVE TO
THROW EVERYTHING AWAY.

04:38.478 --> 04:40.414
IT WAS A MISTAKE,
SELF‐DEFENSE.

04:40.447 --> 04:42.783
IT WASN'T A MISTAKE.
SHE NEVER EVEN SAW IT COMING.

04:42.816 --> 04:45.786
WELL,
MAYBE NO ONE ELSE SAW.

04:45.819 --> 04:47.020
THERE WAS
A SECURITY CAMERA.

04:47.054 --> 04:48.989
Oh, my God!
THIS IS INSANE!

04:49.022 --> 04:52.693
WE CAN'T GO BACK, OKAY?

04:52.726 --> 04:54.027
WE CAN'T GO BACK.

04:54.061 --> 04:56.730
MY DAYS WERE NUMBERED ANYWAY,
AS WERE YOURS

04:56.763 --> 04:59.066
BECAUSE YOU ALL HAVE THE BAD
FORTUNE OF BEING RELATED TO ME.

04:59.099 --> 05:01.969
SO WE CAN'T GO BACK.
WE CAN'T.

05:02.002 --> 05:03.270
[ RADIO TURNS ON ]

05:03.303 --> 05:04.972
Man:
YOU'RE ON RADIO GARAGE SALE.

05:05.005 --> 05:06.139
Woman:
<i>HI, MY NAME IS MARTHA,</i>

05:06.173 --> 05:07.975
<i>AND I HAVE</i>
<i>A LAWN MOWER TO SELL.</i>

05:08.008 --> 05:10.143
[ RADIO TURNS OFF ]

05:12.212 --> 05:16.149
OKAY. THAT'S THE END OF CARDS.
WE'RE POOLING CASH.

05:18.986 --> 05:21.488
NO. NO!

05:21.522 --> 05:23.490
I'M NOT RUINING MY LIFE
BECAUSE OF HIM.

05:23.524 --> 05:27.561
<i>HE</i> MADE THE MISTAKE.
NO ONE'S LOOKING FOR <i>ME.</i>

05:45.646 --> 05:48.182
YOU'RE RIGHT, SILAS.
NO ONE'S LOOKING FOR YOU.

05:48.215 --> 05:50.851
THEY WILL BE LOOKING FOR YOU
IF THEY CAN'T FIND ME.

05:50.884 --> 05:52.619
Nance, we're all tired.

05:52.653 --> 05:54.388
NO. NO. HE'S OLD ENOUGH
TO DECIDE FOR HIMSELF.

05:56.890 --> 05:58.959
I'M NOT GONNA
DRAG YOU ALONG WITH ME.

05:58.992 --> 06:00.794
JUST KNOW,
IF YOU GET OUT NOW,

06:00.827 --> 06:03.997
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU'RE GONNA
BE ABLE TO LIVE A NORMAL LIFE.

06:04.031 --> 06:08.068
YOU'RE STILL GONNA HAVE TO RUN
FOR I...

06:08.101 --> 06:11.205
[ Voice breaking ]
I DON'T KNOW HOW LONG.

06:13.440 --> 06:15.742
YOU MIGHT HAVE A BETTER SHOT
GOING SOLO,

06:15.776 --> 06:17.444
SO YOU DECIDE.

06:17.477 --> 06:19.780
YOU'RE GONNA BE A LONE WOLF OR
YOU'RE GONNA GO WITH THE PACK.

06:19.813 --> 06:21.415
[ HOWLS ]
SHUT UP, SHANE.

06:23.383 --> 06:29.857
I WILL ASK YOU, AS YOUR MOTHER,
WHO WANTS YOU TO LIVE,

06:29.890 --> 06:31.959
THAT YOU NEVER GO BACK
TO REN MAR

06:31.992 --> 06:35.362
OR ANYWHERE, REALLY,
IN THE SAN DIEGO AREA

06:35.395 --> 06:39.700
OR MEXICO,
PROBABLY NOT LOS ANGELES.

07:01.054 --> 07:04.157
[ STEVIE CRYING ]

07:07.895 --> 07:10.364
Silas: LUPITA SLIPPED ME
SOME MONEY.

07:10.397 --> 07:12.699
OH.

07:12.733 --> 07:16.203
WOW. LUPITA.
THAT WAS NICE.

07:23.177 --> 07:26.880
COME ON, MAN.
IT'S GONNA BE FUN.

07:26.914 --> 07:29.850
NEW NAME, NEW IDENTITY.

07:29.883 --> 07:34.454
TOTAL ROAMING,
GYPSY‐STYLE SHENANIGANS.

07:34.488 --> 07:38.859
MAD PLAY FROM THE LADIES
IN STRANGE NEW TOWNS,

07:38.892 --> 07:40.894
STRANGE NEW BEDS.

07:40.928 --> 07:43.997
NO, NO, NO.
SECURITY CAMERAS.

07:44.031 --> 07:45.399
KEEP THE BILL DOWN.
THERE YOU GO.

07:45.432 --> 07:47.634
YOU'RE TOTALLY GONNA ROCK
THE ITINERANT‐OUTLAW LIFESTYLE,

07:47.668 --> 07:48.702
TRUST ME.

07:48.735 --> 07:49.837
UGH! THIS IS LIVING.

07:49.870 --> 07:52.005
NO BAGGAGE.
NO RULES.

07:52.039 --> 07:53.941
WHO EXACTLY IS AFTER US?

07:53.974 --> 07:55.876
OH, OH, OH.
UM, I'M NOT SURE.

07:55.909 --> 07:57.411
YOUR MOTHER HAS
A BETTER HANDLE ON THAT.

07:57.444 --> 08:00.147
GET THOSE PHONES.
AND BATTERIES, TOO.

08:00.180 --> 08:02.883
A WHOLE BUNCH OF THEM ‐‐
9‐VOLT, "D,"

08:02.916 --> 08:04.885
DOUBLE‐A, TRIPLE‐A.

08:04.918 --> 08:06.019
DONE THIS BEFORE?

08:06.053 --> 08:07.154
UH...
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:07.187 --> 08:08.922
NOVA SCOTIA,
SUMMER OF '89.

08:08.956 --> 08:10.858
I'LL BE FRANK ‐‐
THIS IS MY WHEELHOUSE.

08:10.891 --> 08:12.159
I'M THE KING
OF OFF‐GRID LIVING.

08:12.192 --> 08:13.861
OH, INFLATABLE KAYAKS!

08:13.894 --> 08:16.630
OKAY, WE GOT A LINE.

08:16.663 --> 08:18.765
OH, WOW.
VICTORIA'S SECRET.

08:18.799 --> 08:21.201
LUMBER LIQUIDATORS.

08:21.235 --> 08:23.670
HOOTERS? NO HOOTERS?
HOOTERS!

08:29.042 --> 08:30.911
YOU WANT CASH BACK?

08:30.944 --> 08:33.847
OH, HIT "$9,999."

08:33.881 --> 08:35.182
MAX IS $80.

08:35.215 --> 08:39.219
GOT ANY WIGGLE ROOM THERE,
JAZZMINE?

08:40.654 --> 08:42.656
$80 PER <i>TRANSACTION.</i>

08:42.689 --> 08:47.427
I CAN VOID TRANSACTION AND RING
EVERYTHING SEPARATE IF YOU WANT.

08:47.461 --> 08:48.929
CAN WE DO THAT?

08:48.962 --> 08:51.198
SUPPOSED TO GET
MANAGER'S APPROVAL,

08:51.231 --> 08:55.235
BUT I KNOW
HOW TO FAKE IT.

08:59.606 --> 09:01.942
WHAT, UH...

09:01.975 --> 09:05.379
I'M THE CHOSEN ONE
OF WARRIOR GRYPHON.

09:08.615 --> 09:09.683
COOL.

09:09.716 --> 09:12.119
YOU HAVE PRETTY SKIN.

09:13.520 --> 09:15.889
THANK YOU.

09:15.923 --> 09:18.458
THE ROAD, MAN.

09:19.993 --> 09:21.562
ADVENTURES ON THE ROAD.

09:26.934 --> 09:29.303
[ HISSES ]

09:38.712 --> 09:41.248
I TOLD YOU WE SHOULD'VE STACKED
THE DIAPERS ON THE BOTTOM.

09:46.019 --> 09:47.921
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

09:47.955 --> 09:50.524
YOU. OUT.

09:50.557 --> 09:52.092
NOW.

09:53.026 --> 09:55.262
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

09:59.967 --> 10:01.068
OH, MAN.

10:01.101 --> 10:03.103
I WAS WONDERING
WHEN SHE WAS GONNA BLOW.

10:03.136 --> 10:06.306
YEAH.
SHE'S PRETTY PISSED.

10:06.340 --> 10:09.510
WELL, HE BLUDGEONED A WOMAN
TO DEATH WITH A MALLET.

10:09.543 --> 10:11.278
HE SHOULD BE CHASTISED.

10:11.311 --> 10:12.913
LISTEN.

10:12.946 --> 10:14.081
[ SIGHS ]

10:14.114 --> 10:16.817
WHAT YOU DID
WAS NOT OKAY.

10:16.850 --> 10:19.019
IT WAS DANGEROUS
AND FOOLISH,

10:19.052 --> 10:20.921
AND NOW WE'RE ALL
PAYING FOR IT.

10:20.954 --> 10:22.356
WELL, THAT'S NO WAY
TO SAY THANK YOU.

10:22.389 --> 10:23.957
WHAT?

10:23.991 --> 10:26.226
I SAVED YOUR ASS.
I SAVED ALL OUR ASSES.

10:26.960 --> 10:28.028
OH, SHIT.

10:28.061 --> 10:29.663
DO YOU EVEN HEAR YOURSELF?
YOU'RE A KID.

10:29.696 --> 10:31.765
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE OUT
PLAYING BASEBALL,

10:31.798 --> 10:32.933
NOT CLUBBING PEOPLE
TO DEATH.

10:32.966 --> 10:35.202
I'M THE MOTHER.
I DECIDE WHO GETS CLUBBED.

10:35.235 --> 10:37.738
I <i>DO</i> THE CLUBBING,
NOT <i>YOU.</i>

10:37.771 --> 10:40.307
WHEN YOU'RE 18 ‐‐
UH, 21 ‐‐

10:40.340 --> 10:41.909
FEEL FREE
TO TAKE A STICK...

10:41.942 --> 10:43.010
CROQUET MALLET!

10:43.043 --> 10:44.144
...WHATEVER SPORTING GOOD
YOU DESIRE,

10:44.178 --> 10:45.312
CLUB WHOEVER YOU LIKE,

10:45.345 --> 10:47.581
GO TO PRISON FOR THE REST
OF YOUR LIFE.

10:47.614 --> 10:48.916
BUT MEANTIME,
YOUR ONLY JOB

10:48.949 --> 10:50.984
IS TO DO KID THINGS ‐‐

10:51.018 --> 10:53.654
VIDEO GAMES,
BROKEN CURFEWS,

10:53.687 --> 10:55.155
PEEPS IN THE MICROWAVE.

10:55.189 --> 10:57.824
THAT WAS MY MESS TO FIX,
NOT YOURS.

10:57.858 --> 11:00.260
AM I GROUNDED?

11:00.961 --> 11:02.095
OHHH.

11:02.129 --> 11:04.598
EMPTY THOSE POCKETS.

11:04.631 --> 11:06.200
NO!
DO IT!

11:11.572 --> 11:13.841
NO MORE SUGAR FOR YOU.

11:13.874 --> 11:16.176
BUT YOU'RE GLAD
I DID IT.

11:16.210 --> 11:20.514
I'M GLAD IT WAS DONE,
NOT BY <i>YOU.</i>

11:22.783 --> 11:26.720
DON'T SMILE.
TURN AROUND.

11:26.753 --> 11:29.289
DON'T DO IT AGAIN!

11:29.323 --> 11:31.358
GO.

11:33.861 --> 11:39.466
OKAY. TIME FOR UNCLE ANDY'S
GUIDE TO LIVING OFF THE GRID.

11:39.499 --> 11:43.170
STEP ONE ‐‐
KILL YOUR OLD IDENTITY.

11:43.203 --> 11:46.006
FROM HERE ON IN,
THE BOTWINS ARE DEAD.

11:46.039 --> 11:49.676
THAT MEANS NO CONTACTING
FRIENDS OR FAMILY.

11:49.710 --> 11:50.944
WE DON'T HAVE
ANY FRIENDS OR FAMILY.

11:50.978 --> 11:52.179
I'M FRIENDS WITH ISABEL.

11:52.212 --> 11:55.215
OH, YOU CAN'T CONTACT ISABEL,
HONEY. SORRY.

11:55.249 --> 11:57.251
WELL, THAT MEANS
YOU CAN'T CONTACT CELIA.

11:57.284 --> 11:59.319
NO PROBLEM.

11:59.353 --> 12:00.387
MOVING ON.

12:00.420 --> 12:03.757
STEP TWO ‐‐
ESTABLISHING NEW IDENTITIES.

12:03.790 --> 12:04.958
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

12:04.992 --> 12:06.393
IF WE GET ON THE 84
IN PORTLAND,

12:06.426 --> 12:07.895
IT'LL TAKE US
BACK TO THE 80.

12:07.928 --> 12:09.897
UH, WE'RE NOT GOING
TO PITTSBURGH.

12:09.930 --> 12:11.798
WE'RE GOING TO...

12:11.832 --> 12:13.233
CANADA.

12:13.267 --> 12:16.970
CANADA?!
THIS...IS BULLSHIT.
NO, IT ISN'T.

12:17.004 --> 12:18.238
WE KILLED SOMEONE
VERY IMPORTANT,

12:18.272 --> 12:20.374
AND WE DON'T HAVE ESTEBAN
TO HELP US.

12:20.407 --> 12:21.175
"WE"?

12:21.208 --> 12:22.543
HE KILLED SOMEONE,

12:22.576 --> 12:25.512
AND WE'RE NOT EVEN SURE
IF ANYONE IS FOLLOWING US.

12:25.546 --> 12:26.713
PSYCHOPATH.

12:26.747 --> 12:28.949
ESTEBAN'S NOT GONNA BE HAPPY
THAT YOU TOOK HIS CHILD.

12:28.982 --> 12:30.984
MY CHILD.
AND YOUR BROTHER.

12:31.018 --> 12:33.854
HALF.
OH, LET'S NOT MAKE
THAT DISTINCTION, OKAY?

12:33.887 --> 12:36.456
IT'S PETTY.
SHANE, HONEY, GET US TO CANADA.

12:36.490 --> 12:37.958
KEEP GOING NORTH.

12:37.991 --> 12:39.626
WHAT THE HELL
IS IN CANADA?

12:39.660 --> 12:44.131
DISTANCE BETWEEN US
AND WHAT HAPPENED LAST NIGHT.

12:44.164 --> 12:46.900
WE COULD DRIVE
TO ALASKA OR ARGENTINA ‐‐

12:46.934 --> 12:48.335
BOTH GOOD PLACES
TO DISAPPEAR.

12:48.368 --> 12:51.872
PANAMA CANAL!
LET'S DO A SEVEN WONDERS TOUR!

12:51.905 --> 12:53.140
SORRY. NO WONDERS.

12:53.173 --> 12:55.008
ARGENTINA REQUIRES GOING
THROUGH MEXICO,

12:55.042 --> 12:56.109
WHICH IS OUT
OF THE QUESTION.

12:56.143 --> 12:57.845
ALASKA, HOWEVER,
STILL ON THE TABLE.

12:57.878 --> 12:59.112
NO, IT'S NOT.
WHY?

12:59.146 --> 13:02.049
LONG STORY INVOLVING
A CANNERY FOREMAN IN KODIAK

13:02.082 --> 13:06.053
AND A KNIFE FIGHT
IN A SALMON SMOKEHOUSE.

13:06.086 --> 13:09.623
"IF I EVER CATCH YOU
IN THIS STATE AGAIN"...

13:09.656 --> 13:10.858
IT'S NOT WORTH
TALKING ABOUT.

13:10.891 --> 13:12.492
Right.

13:18.065 --> 13:20.934
HOW ARE WE SUPPOSED TO
BUY ANYTHING

13:20.968 --> 13:24.972
WITH NOT MUCH U. S. CASH
AND NO CREDIT CARDS...

13:25.005 --> 13:26.440
IN CANADA?

13:26.473 --> 13:27.708
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:27.741 --> 13:30.477
NOT REBUILDING YET.

13:30.511 --> 13:31.912
STILL FLEEING.

13:31.945 --> 13:34.014
NEED TIME
TO WORK OUT THE DETAILS.

13:34.047 --> 13:36.416
I SHOULD'VE GOTTEN OUT
BACK IN CALIFORNIA.

13:36.450 --> 13:38.752
WATCH YOUR MOVIE,
SWEETHEART.

13:40.988 --> 13:42.322
[ VIDEO PLAYS ]

13:42.356 --> 13:46.293
All: "THE DODGE CARAVAN'S
THIRD‐ROW SPLIT‐BENCH SEATING

13:46.326 --> 13:49.129
"MAY ALSO BE FLIPPED
COMPLETELY REARWARD

13:49.162 --> 13:54.468
FOR CONVENIENT,
COMFORTABLE TAILGATE SEATING."

13:54.501 --> 13:56.570
[ VIDEO STOPS ]

14:06.180 --> 14:07.948
YOU, BACK.
ME, FRONT.
NO.

14:07.981 --> 14:09.583
I'M NOT ASKING.
I'M TELLING.

14:09.616 --> 14:11.351
HOW ABOUT A "PLEASE"?

14:11.385 --> 14:13.620
HOW ABOUT RESPECT AND FEAR
FOR YOUR FUCKING MOTHER?

14:13.654 --> 14:14.821
SWITCH WITH ME.

14:14.855 --> 14:16.857
NO. NO. I'M MORE
THAN CAPABLE ‐‐ DON'T!

14:16.890 --> 14:18.525
OFF! SHE'S COMING.
BE COOL.

14:18.559 --> 14:20.961
WELL, ALL RIGHT, GOOD FOLKS,
LET'S JUST DO THE DRILL.

14:20.994 --> 14:22.996
PASSPORTS AND WHERE YA FROM,
WHERE YA HEADED?

14:23.030 --> 14:27.634
WE ARE FROM CALIFORN‐I‐A,

14:27.668 --> 14:28.936
HEADED...

14:28.969 --> 14:30.204
TO CALGARY.
YEAH.

14:30.237 --> 14:31.505
YOU JUST MISSED
THE STAMPEDE.

14:31.538 --> 14:32.506
AWW.
AWW.

14:32.539 --> 14:34.708
SO, UH, HOW DO Y'ALL
KNOW EACH OTHER,

14:34.741 --> 14:36.977
AND, UH,
WHAT BRINGS YOU TO CALGARY?

14:37.010 --> 14:38.612
THESE ARE MY SONS.
WELL, MY WIFE AND I ‐‐

14:38.645 --> 14:41.648
WE'RE HEADED TO A BIRTHDAY
PARTY ‐‐ MY GREAT UNCLE'S.

14:41.682 --> 14:43.483
IT'S AT A NURSING HOME.
SILAS.

14:43.517 --> 14:45.018
92 YEARS YOUNG.

14:45.052 --> 14:47.621
AND, UH,
IT'S TONIGHT AT 8:00.

14:47.654 --> 14:48.922
GORDON LIGHTFOOT'S
PLAYING.

14:48.956 --> 14:49.990
HE'S NEVER MET THE BABY.

14:50.023 --> 14:51.925
LET'S SEE THE LITTLE
BUNDLE OF LOVE.

14:51.959 --> 14:53.861
4 MONTHS. STEVIE.
HOLD HIM UP, HONEY.

14:53.894 --> 14:57.331
HOLD HIM UP.
LET'S SEE HIS FACE.

14:57.364 --> 14:59.933
LET'S JUST TAKE A PEEK
AT THE LITTLE TYKE'S
BIRTH CERTIFICATE,

14:59.967 --> 15:02.202
AND I'LL GET YOU
ON YOUR WAY.

15:06.773 --> 15:10.377
UH...
I THINK YOU'VE GOT IT.

15:10.410 --> 15:12.646
NO. MUST BE IN YOUR PURSE,
SWEETHEART.

15:12.679 --> 15:15.382
YEAH, I DON'T ‐‐

15:15.415 --> 15:17.818
I DON'T SEE IT.

15:17.851 --> 15:19.152
UH‐OH.
SOMEONE'S IN THE DOGHOUSE.

15:19.186 --> 15:21.255
DO WE REALLY NEED IT?

15:21.288 --> 15:23.190
HE'S OBVIOUSLY GOT
HIS, UH, FATHER'S SMILE.

15:23.223 --> 15:24.958
STOP, SWEETIE.
HIS SMILE IS ALL YOURS.

15:24.992 --> 15:26.860
OH, I THINK THE EYES ARE MINE.
THE CHIN IS YOURS.

15:26.894 --> 15:28.195
I'M NOT SURE
THAT I AGREE.

15:28.228 --> 15:29.496
I'M REAL SORRY, FOLKS.

15:29.530 --> 15:32.165
I CAN'T LET YOU OVER
WITHOUT THE BIRTH CERTIFICATE.

15:32.199 --> 15:35.035
LOOK, UH,
W‐WAS HE BORN IN THE STATES?

15:35.068 --> 15:36.904
YES, IN A HOSPITAL,
ON THE GRID.

15:36.937 --> 15:39.540
ALL RIGHT,
I DON'T USUALLY DO THIS,

15:39.573 --> 15:43.610
BUT IF YOU CALL THE HOSPITAL
AND HAVE THEM FAX IT OVER,

15:43.644 --> 15:46.180
I'LL GET YOU
RIGHT THROUGH.

15:46.213 --> 15:47.181
UM...

15:47.214 --> 15:49.316
ALL RIGHT, TURN‐AROUND POINT'S
RIGHT UP THERE.

15:49.349 --> 15:50.984
YEAH.
AND I'LL SEE YA SOON!

15:51.018 --> 15:53.253
OKAY, THANKS.

15:58.992 --> 16:01.495
WE COULD PUT THE BABY
IN A COOLER,

16:01.528 --> 16:03.997
SEDATE HIM WITH COUGH SYRUP,
TAPE IT SHUT,

16:04.031 --> 16:06.533
PUT TINY AIR HOLES
IN THE TOP.

16:06.567 --> 16:07.701
TINY AIR HOLES!

16:07.734 --> 16:08.969
THAT'S THE SPIRIT!

16:09.002 --> 16:11.338
YOU'RE A MURDERER,
BUT YOU GOT MOXIE, KID.

16:11.371 --> 16:13.774
NOW,
WHERE CAN WE GET A COOLER?

16:13.807 --> 16:15.175
CANADA'S OFF.

16:15.209 --> 16:16.410
WHY?

16:16.443 --> 16:21.081
Mrs. Reyes, this is
Agent Lipschitz from the FBI.

16:21.114 --> 16:23.450
We're currently investigating
<i>a fatality.</i>

16:23.483 --> 16:26.653
Your husband said you
and your sons were on vacation.

16:26.687 --> 16:29.923
<i>I trust you've remained</i>
<i>within U. S. borders.</i>

16:29.957 --> 16:31.391
<i>Please give me a call</i>
<i>when you get this.</i>

16:31.425 --> 16:33.894
My number is ‐‐
WHAT THE FUCK?!

16:33.927 --> 16:36.663
UGH! THEY CAN TRACE US
FROM TOWERS!

16:36.697 --> 16:38.732
PHONES, EVERYONE!

16:38.765 --> 16:40.667
UGH!

16:40.701 --> 16:43.370
NAH!

16:43.403 --> 16:45.539
SIM CARD.

16:45.572 --> 16:46.907
FRIED.

16:46.940 --> 16:50.077
MUCH SIMPLER.
LESS DESTRUCTIVE.

16:56.149 --> 16:57.885
I THINK I'M GONNA
SHAVE MY HEAD.

16:57.918 --> 16:58.952
OOH.
YOU'LL BE SO HARDCORE.

16:58.986 --> 17:00.521
MAYBE YOU SHOULD GET
A SWITCHBLADE...

17:00.554 --> 17:01.822
THAT FLIPS OUT
OF A COMB.

17:01.855 --> 17:04.324
OR MAYBE YOU SHOULD JUST
GET A COMB THAT LOOKS
LIKE A SWITCHBLADE

17:04.358 --> 17:06.260
SO YOU DON'T ACCIDENTLY
CUT YOURSELF.

17:06.293 --> 17:07.394
SHUT UP!

17:07.427 --> 17:08.629
LICK MY BALLS.

17:09.796 --> 17:11.598
DON'T MAKE ME GO PILAR
ON YOUR ASS!

17:11.632 --> 17:12.966
OKAY.

17:13.000 --> 17:15.235
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!

17:15.269 --> 17:16.737
OKAY!

17:16.770 --> 17:19.940
ALL IS MELLOW.

17:19.973 --> 17:21.942
HERE. NEW SOCKS.

17:21.975 --> 17:24.444
NO, DON'T SHAVE YOUR HEAD.

17:24.478 --> 17:26.480
CHICKS LIKE SOMETHING
TO GRAB ON TO.

17:26.513 --> 17:28.482
LOOK FOR THE REMOTE.
MAYBE "TAXI DRIVER'S" ON.

17:28.515 --> 17:29.616
OBJECT LESSON.

17:29.650 --> 17:31.285
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.
THAT WAS <i>ME.</i>

17:31.318 --> 17:33.187
[ DOOR OPENS ]

17:41.428 --> 17:42.996
WELL?
[ LAUGHS ]

17:43.030 --> 17:45.632
NO. NO, NO.

17:45.666 --> 17:47.034
THAT LOOKS FAKE
AND HOOKERY ‐‐

17:47.067 --> 17:48.569
UNLESS THAT'S WHAT
YOU'RE GOING FOR.

17:48.602 --> 17:51.138
SHUT UP.
I LIKE IT.

17:51.171 --> 17:53.640
NEW NAMES, FAMILY.
WHO WE GONNA BE?

17:53.674 --> 17:55.042
I ALWAYS HATED "PRICE."

17:55.075 --> 17:57.377
AND "BOTWIN" WAS SO ‐‐

17:57.411 --> 17:59.079
HEY,
DON'T PISS ON "BOTWIN."

17:59.112 --> 18:01.915
I‐I JUST HATED
ALWAYS HAVING TO SPELL IT.

18:01.949 --> 18:05.419
Nancy: B‐O‐T‐‐
WE NEED
SOMETHING MEANINGFUL.

18:05.452 --> 18:07.187
METAPHORIC.

18:07.221 --> 18:10.357
"PHOENIX."
"ERIC PHOENIX."

18:10.390 --> 18:12.492
NO, "CLIVE."

18:12.526 --> 18:14.962
"STEED."
"CLIVE STEED."

18:14.995 --> 18:16.230
NO, TOTAL PORN NAME.

18:16.263 --> 18:17.998
YOU WANT TO CHOOSE A NAME
THAT SOUNDS LIKE YOUR OWN

18:18.031 --> 18:20.000
SO THAT WHEN PEOPLE CALL YOU,
YOU RESPOND.

18:20.033 --> 18:22.769
I'LL BE "SHAWN."

18:22.803 --> 18:25.572
"SHAWN NEWMAN."

18:25.606 --> 18:26.974
NEW MAN.

18:27.007 --> 18:30.077
"NEWMAN" LIKE ALFRED E.
OR PAUL?

18:30.110 --> 18:31.678
LIKE RANDY.
"SHORT PEOPLE."

18:31.712 --> 18:33.547
YES,
I'LL BE RANDY NEWMAN!

18:33.580 --> 18:34.982
HA! N‐E‐W‐M‐A‐N.

18:35.015 --> 18:37.651
HERITAGE MUDDY.
JEW? AH, CAN'T TELL.

18:37.684 --> 18:39.920
NATHALIE.

18:39.953 --> 18:43.590
FRENCH SPELLING ‐‐
N‐A‐T‐H‐‐ Silent "H."

18:43.624 --> 18:46.026
"NATHALIE NEWMAN."

18:46.059 --> 18:50.864
STEVIE, YOU'RE..."AVI."

18:50.898 --> 18:53.166
NOT THAT YOU KNOW YOUR NAME YET,
BUT YOU WILL.

18:53.200 --> 18:56.003
I LOVE THAT YOU SLEEP
ALL THE TIME.

18:56.036 --> 18:58.839
I KNOW A MOTHER'S NOT
SUPPOSED TO SAY THAT,

18:58.872 --> 19:01.141
BUT I DO.

19:04.044 --> 19:06.013
I'LL BE "MIKE."

19:06.046 --> 19:08.715
"MIKE NEWMAN."

19:08.749 --> 19:10.083
OKAY, MIKE.

19:10.117 --> 19:13.754
THE NEWMAN FAMILY.

19:28.335 --> 19:30.737
MIKE, WILL YOU
HAND ME THE SALT?

19:30.771 --> 19:32.973
SURE, RANDY.

19:33.006 --> 19:35.008
SHAWN,
YOU GONNA GET A REFILL?

19:35.042 --> 19:37.010
I DON'T THINK SO, MIKE.
NATHALIE?

19:37.044 --> 19:39.680
UH, "MOM" IS FINE.

19:39.713 --> 19:43.550
NEWMANS,
HAND ME YOUR OLD I. D. s.

19:43.584 --> 19:47.554
ATM CARDS, LIBRARY CARDS,
EVERYTHING WITH YOUR OLD NAMES.

19:49.723 --> 19:51.058
MIKE?

19:51.091 --> 19:53.160
DRIVER'S LICENSE?

19:53.193 --> 19:55.863
TOOK ME THREE TIMES
TO PASS THE WRITTEN TEST.

19:55.896 --> 19:57.764
MIKE, HONEY.

19:57.798 --> 19:59.433
NO.
I MIGHT NEED IT.

19:59.466 --> 20:03.504
WHAT YOU'LL NEED, MIKE, IS
MIKE NEWMAN'S DRIVER'S LICENSE,

20:03.537 --> 20:06.507
WHICH COULD BE
A CLASS "A," "D," OR "M,"

20:06.540 --> 20:09.109
MEANING MIKE'S LICENSE
WILL ALLOW HIM TO DRIVE TRUCKS

20:09.142 --> 20:10.544
AND BUSES
AND MOTORCYCLES,

20:10.577 --> 20:13.213
WHICH SILAS BOTWIN'S
PUSSY LICENSE DOES NOT.

20:13.247 --> 20:15.349
YOU WANT TO BE
AN ICE‐ROAD TRUCKER OR NOT?

20:15.382 --> 20:16.884
OKAY.

20:16.917 --> 20:19.686
NOW...LET A MASTER
GET TO WORK.

20:23.257 --> 20:24.591
HOLA!

20:28.562 --> 20:30.163
GOT THE FAKE‐I. D. GUY.

20:31.899 --> 20:34.201
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

20:46.914 --> 20:49.416
GOOD COVER.

20:52.052 --> 20:54.421
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

21:01.028 --> 21:02.696
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

21:02.729 --> 21:03.864
Woman: I'M COMING!

21:03.897 --> 21:07.434
SORRY.
I HAD THE BLENDER GOING.

21:07.467 --> 21:09.303
IS THIS 620?

21:09.336 --> 21:10.437
IT SURE IS.

21:10.470 --> 21:12.072
SORRY. I ‐‐

21:12.105 --> 21:14.975
YOU FOLKS LOOKING
FOR THE CHINAMAN?

21:16.009 --> 21:18.145
RIGHT THIS WAY.

21:21.548 --> 21:22.916
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

21:22.950 --> 21:24.885
BILLY, HONEY?

21:24.918 --> 21:27.020
Billy:
THE FUCK DO YOU WANT?

21:27.054 --> 21:28.288
[ LOCK DISENGAGES ]

21:28.322 --> 21:31.158
OH.

21:36.597 --> 21:38.098
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

21:40.634 --> 21:42.569
WHY "THE CHINAMAN"?

21:42.603 --> 21:44.571
WHY NOT?

21:44.605 --> 21:46.773
YOU'RE NOT CHINESE.

21:46.807 --> 21:48.308
AND YOU'RE NOT MIKE,
MIKE.

21:49.943 --> 21:51.912
$320.

21:51.945 --> 21:53.013
THREE HUNDRED TWENTY?

21:53.046 --> 21:55.916
$80 EACH.
I ALREADY TOLD YOU THAT.

21:55.949 --> 21:57.284
I GOT $190.

21:57.317 --> 22:00.854
THAT'LL GET YOU THREE.
YOU CAN CHOOSE WHICH
ONES YOU WANT.

22:00.888 --> 22:03.957
DON'T MAKE ME
PRESS THIS BUTTON.

22:03.991 --> 22:06.226
NO, WE DON'T WANT
THE BUTTON.

22:06.260 --> 22:08.362
WAIT.

22:08.395 --> 22:10.130
I HAVE GOT...

22:11.965 --> 22:13.066
...LUMBER LIQUIDATORS...

22:13.100 --> 22:15.869
OR SUNGLASS HUT...

22:15.903 --> 22:18.639
OR HOOTERS.

22:18.672 --> 22:19.873
[ SIGHS ]

22:19.907 --> 22:23.243
I GOT FOUR OF THOSE.
YOU CAN HAVE THREE.

22:23.277 --> 22:24.811
MOM?!

22:24.845 --> 22:26.013
Woman: WHAT?

22:26.046 --> 22:26.880
HOOTERS GIFT CARDS?!

22:26.914 --> 22:28.148
SWIPE 'EM FIRST!

22:28.182 --> 22:29.583
DO WE TAKE THEM?!

22:29.616 --> 22:32.052
SURE!

22:48.702 --> 22:52.840
YITGADDAL VEYITQADDASH
SHMEH RABBA.

22:52.873 --> 22:55.409
SHANE GREGORY BOTWIN ‐‐

22:55.442 --> 22:57.311
HIS SCHOOL I.D.
FROM EIGHTH GRADE.

22:57.344 --> 23:00.280
A LIKABLE BOY
WITH SADNESS IN HIS SOUL.

23:00.314 --> 23:03.984
CONFUSED, FRUSTRATED,
IMPULSIVE.

23:04.017 --> 23:07.254
WE MOURN
SHANE GREGORY BOTWIN...

23:09.890 --> 23:12.960
...AND SAY BARUCH HABA
TO SHAWN OLIVER NEWMAN.

23:12.993 --> 23:15.863
MAY YOU LIVE TO SEE
YOUR DREAMS FULFILLED.

23:15.896 --> 23:17.064
THIS IS
A DRIVER'S LICENSE,

23:17.097 --> 23:18.932
SO YOU SHOULD PROBABLY
LEARN TO DRIVE NOW.

23:18.966 --> 23:21.068
SILAS.

23:21.101 --> 23:23.937
YITGADDAL,
ET CETERA, ET CETERA.

23:23.971 --> 23:27.941
SILAS ANDREW BOTWIN,
FIRSTBORN SON...

23:27.975 --> 23:30.911
A GREEN THUMB...

23:30.944 --> 23:32.513
AN OPEN
AND WILLING HEART.

23:32.546 --> 23:36.283
THE BEST PARTS OF YOU
WILL CARRY FORWARD.

23:36.316 --> 23:39.386
THE REST WE DO COMMIT
TO FIRE.

23:39.419 --> 23:43.023
AND SHIT HOWDY
TO MIKE T. NEWMAN.

23:43.056 --> 23:46.093
NO ONE KNOWS
WHAT THE "T" STANDS FOR.

23:46.126 --> 23:49.696
MAZEL TOV.
HERE YOU GO.

23:56.637 --> 24:00.240
NANCY PRICE BOTWIN.

24:02.743 --> 24:05.012
FAREWELL, PANTS...

24:05.045 --> 24:06.980
AND ALL THAT YOU WERE.

24:09.650 --> 24:11.351
YOU HAD MANY POCKETS.

24:11.385 --> 24:14.154
[ DRIVER'S LICENSE CLATTERS ]

24:14.188 --> 24:17.524
AND WARM, WONDERFUL WELCOME
TO NATHALIE NEWMAN, SILENT "H,"

24:17.558 --> 24:21.228
DANCER, MOTHER,
LOVER OF THE OPEN ROAD.

24:25.065 --> 24:27.134
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
THE NEWMAN FAMILY.

24:31.939 --> 24:32.973
GOOD.

24:33.006 --> 24:36.643
OKAY, HOLD HANDS.

24:36.677 --> 24:38.011
BARUCH ATAH ADONAI ELOHEINU
MELECH HA‐OLAM ‐‐

24:38.045 --> 24:39.446
LET'S GO.
WE GET IT.
YEAH.

24:39.479 --> 24:41.515
WELL, WE'RE NOT
A MINYAN, ANYWAY.

24:41.548 --> 24:45.285
UM...

24:45.319 --> 24:48.555
THE NEWMANS WILL SUCCEED
WHERE THE BOTWINS FAILED.

24:48.589 --> 24:51.558
THEY WILL LIVE
A NORMAL LIFE.

24:51.592 --> 24:53.293
THEY WILL FIND JOBS.

24:53.327 --> 24:56.730
THEY WILL...

24:56.763 --> 24:59.099
[ Voice breaking ]
...GO TO SCHOOL.

24:59.132 --> 25:01.869
THEY WILL HAVE HOBBIES.

25:01.902 --> 25:06.340
THEY WILL LIVE A QUIET,
UNDER‐THE‐RADAR LIFE.

25:06.373 --> 25:10.177
THE NEWMANS...
WILL BE A FAMILY.

25:20.354 --> 25:23.924
WHAT IF I'M HAVING SECOND
THOUGHTS ABOUT BEING MIKE?

25:23.957 --> 25:25.893
IT'S TOO LATE, MICHAEL.

25:25.926 --> 25:27.394
WE'RE OUT
OF HOOTERS GIFT CARDS.

25:34.301 --> 25:37.171
Lipschitz: YOU HAD
VERY CLOSE TIES TO HER

25:37.204 --> 25:38.672
WITHIN YOUR ORGANIZATION.

25:38.705 --> 25:44.244
SHE WAS PIVOTAL IN FINANCING
YOUR BID FOR GOVERNOR.

25:44.278 --> 25:47.347
THE RECORDS ARE PUBLIC.

25:47.381 --> 25:52.019
YOU REALLY HAVE NOTHING TO SAY
ABOUT HER DEATH?

25:52.052 --> 25:55.656
AGENT LIPSCHITZ,
MY CLIENT IS A VERY BUSY MAN.

25:57.457 --> 26:01.428
IF YOU REMEMBER ANYTHING
FROM THAT NIGHT, MR. REYES,

26:01.461 --> 26:04.965
IF ANYTHING SUDDENLY
OCCURS TO YOU,

26:04.998 --> 26:06.967
PLEASE DON'T HESITATE
TO CONTACT US.

26:07.000 --> 26:10.437
THIS DEATH OCCURRED
ON AMERICAN SOIL,

26:10.470 --> 26:14.942
SO IT'S VERY IMPORTANT
THAT WE FIND OUT WHAT HAPPENED.

26:14.975 --> 26:16.944
YEAH.

26:16.977 --> 26:18.245
OF COURSE.

26:18.278 --> 26:23.016
YOUR WIFE, MR. REYES ‐‐
IS SHE STILL ON VACATION?

26:23.050 --> 26:24.985
YES, SHE IS.

26:25.018 --> 26:26.286
WHEN'S SHE DUE BACK?

26:26.320 --> 26:27.888
TONIGHT.

26:27.921 --> 26:30.023
WE'VE LEFT HER A MESSAGE.

26:30.057 --> 26:32.826
DO ASK HER TO CALL
WHEN YOU SPEAK TO HER NEXT.

26:32.860 --> 26:36.029
OR...

26:36.063 --> 26:37.898
COME SEE US
IN THE MORNING.

26:37.931 --> 26:40.100
I'M HERE AT 8:00.

26:40.133 --> 26:43.036
I'LL LET HER KNOW.

26:49.943 --> 26:51.745
FIND THE WIFE.

26:55.382 --> 26:57.818
GO GET HER.

26:57.851 --> 27:00.187
GET MY SON.

27:01.321 --> 27:04.992
♪♪ HEY, BOY,
WHERE'S YOUR GIRLFRIEND? ♪♪

27:05.025 --> 27:07.794
♪♪ SHE NEEDS YOUR ATTENTION ♪♪

27:07.828 --> 27:13.100
♪♪ HEY, BOY, WHERE'S YOUR
LITTLE GIRL TONIGHT? ♪♪

27:13.133 --> 27:16.270
♪♪ MY STEADY GIRL ♪♪

27:16.303 --> 27:19.706
♪♪ DON'T ALWAYS SAY ♪♪

27:19.740 --> 27:21.975
♪♪ THAT SHE'S IN LOVE WITH ME ♪♪

27:22.009 --> 27:25.913
♪♪ BUT I CAN FEEL IT
IN THE WAY ♪♪

27:25.946 --> 27:27.881
♪♪ IS SHE TELLIN' LIES? ♪♪

27:27.915 --> 27:30.951
♪♪ NO, NO,
SHE WOULDN'T DO THAT ♪♪

27:30.984 --> 27:33.854
♪♪ AND BESIDES,
I'M COOLER THAN THEM ♪♪

